Best Practices by Functionality Category
Transaction Monitoring Alert TriageTrigger: Rules engine or ML score breach above configured threshold. Action: L1 analyst reviews customer profile, prior SARs, peer-group deviation score, and transaction narrative. Escalates or closes with a reason code and documented rationale. Owner: AML Analyst L1. Output: Closed alert with reason code OR escalated case file. SLA: High-risk 24h, Medium 72h, Low 7 days.
Sanctions & PEP ScreeningTrigger: Customer onboarding, transaction initiation, or watchlist update event. Action: Automated fuzzy-match against active lists. Scores ≥ 0.7 queue for analyst review; exact matches trigger instant block. Analyst verifies identity and documents clear/block decision with rationale. Owner: Sanctions Analyst. Output: Clear / Block / EDD-required decision with documented evidence. SLA: Instant block; review within 4 hours; EDD within 5 business days.
KYC / CDD / EDDTrigger: New customer onboarding, periodic review cycle, or risk-rating change event. Action: Standard CDD for all customers. EDD triggered automatically for PEPs, high-risk jurisdictions, complex ownership structures, or cash-intensive businesses. EDD pack includes source-of-wealth, business purpose, and UBO verification. Owner: KYC Analyst / Relationship Manager (EDD sign-off by MLRO). Output: Customer risk rating + review frequency + documented evidence file. SLA: CDD same-day; EDD within 5-10 business days.
Case Management & InvestigationTrigger: Alert escalation from L1 or direct referral from relationship manager. Action: L2 investigator builds case file: alert history, KYC profile, network analysis, transaction narrative. Determines SAR / no-SAR within SLA with full documented rationale. Owner: AML Investigator L2, reviewed by MLRO. Output: Closed case with rationale OR SAR submitted to FIU. SLA: 30 days from case creation (regulatory deadline varies by jurisdiction).
SAR / STR FilingTrigger: MLRO approval of investigator's SAR recommendation. Action: Compliance officer drafts SAR narrative covering: who, what, when, how much, why suspicious. MLRO reviews for completeness, regulatory format compliance, and tipping-off risk. Files via secure portal to FIU. Owner: Compliance Officer (draft) + MLRO (approval). Output: Filed SAR with FIU acknowledgment. Internal copy retained for audit. SLA: Within 30 days of suspicion crystallising (jurisdiction-dependent).
Model GovernanceTrigger: Scheduled validation cycle (minimum annual) or detected performance drift (PSI > 0.2). Action: Model risk team reviews detection rate, false positive rate, Gini coefficient, and population stability. Retrains or recalibrates model. Documents validation outcome under SR 11-7 / SS1/23 framework. Owner: Model Risk Officer. Output: Validated model version in registry with approval sign-off. SLA: Annual minimum; triggered within 30 days of drift detection.
Audit & ExplainabilityTrigger: Every decision event — human or AI-generated. Action: System writes immutable log entry: actor identity, decision inputs, model version used, rationale text, confidence score (AI), and timestamp. Log is tamper-evident and regulator-accessible on demand. Owner: System (automated) + Internal Audit (quarterly review). Output: Regulator-ready audit pack exportable per investigation or per period.
 
